TULAREMIA, HARES - NORTHERN ITALY
*********************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Thu, 08 Jan 1998 08:50:54 +0100
From: Pasquale Urbano <micro@CESIT1.UNIFI.IT>
Source: La Nazione, January 7, 1998

Routine veterinary surveillance in the Voghera district (Northern Italy)
has found several tularemia-infected hares in a shipment from Hungary which
had been released into the wild. A few dead hares have been found in the
area. Family doctors have been alerted. Press coverage, although not
completely accurate, seems adequate to warn the general public of the risks
involved.
In the past, imported wildlife has introduced tularemia in some areas of
Tuscany, which became endozoonotic for several years; clusters of human
cases were traced to ingestion of water from springs contaminated by
infected animals.
--
Pasquale Urbano
