[I have no problem with this but as the hares "had been released" before
they were found to be "tularemia-infected", how do we know that these were
not domestic Italian dead hares? Were the imported Hungarian hares tatooed
or ear-notched or ear-tagged? Was this area previously hare-free? What was
the basis for this epidemiological decision? - Mod.MHJ]
